US President Donald Trump has again voiced his claim of voter fraud in the United States Presidential Election, saying his administration will head to the Supreme Court to stop all voting and ensure the integrity of the polls. Trump was addressing the media in Washington DC. “We were getting ready for a big celebration, we were winning everything and all of a sudden it was just called off…” Trump expressed his elation over wins in the key state of Florida and others including Ohio, Georgia, North Carolina and in Pennsylvania, where he said they are leading by a tremendous amount of votes. Vote counting is still underway. Trump also made claims of his wins not being tabulated in Texas, as he outlines in the video below:  